UUIDs (Universally Unique Identifiers), not cryptographic public keys. Here's the distinction:


0c67ed5d-81ac-4d6d-9991-be4956c970c3  ← UUID (just a unique ID, not a key)
UUID — randomly generated 128-bit identifier. Used to:

Name the org's storage folder
Link records across tables (clients, dossiers, documents all have organization_id pointing to this)
Identify the org in API requests

